        "title": "feat(desktop): add Tauri desktop companion MVP",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a new Tauri v2 desktop companion app under `apps/desktop/` for a Linux/Windows MVP.\n- Embed the existing Gateway Control UI in a React + Tailwind shell with gateway restart and health-status wiring.\n- Tray integration, close-to-tray behavior, and gateway-config discovery from `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n- Root `desktop:dev` / `desktop:build` scripts and pnpm workspace registration.\n\n## Supersedes\n- Supersedes #59075 and openclaw fork PR `BingqingLyu/openclaw#1795`.\n- Rebased cleanly onto current `main`; `pnpm-lock.yaml` regenerated against current `main`.\n\n## Review feedback addressed (from #59075)\n- **P1 listener race in `App.tsx`** — `listenForGatewayStatus` returns a promise; under React StrictMode the previous code could orphan the listener. Now we call `unlisten()` immediately if the effect has already torn down before the promise resolves.\n- **P1 CSP disabled** — `tauri.conf.json` `csp: null` replaced with a minimal allowlist (self + loopback gateway + tauri ipc + `data:` for fonts/images).\n- **P1 panic on `customBindHost`** — `build_dashboard_url` now returns `Result<String, String>`; errors flow into `GatewaySnapshot::error` instead of panicking. Added `format_host_for_url` so bare IPv6 hosts like `::1` are bracketed before `Url::parse`.\n- **P2 reqwest client rebuilt every probe** — health probes now share a single `reqwest::blocking::Client` via `OnceLock`.\n- **P2 token leak in displayed URL** — `App.tsx` redacts `#token=...` in the on-screen header while still passing the full URL to the iframe `src`.\n\n## Validation\n- `cargo fmt --manifest-path apps/desktop/src-tauri/Cargo.toml --check` ✅\n- `cargo check` requires Linux GTK system deps (`libglib2.0-dev`, `libgobject-2.0-dev`, `libwebkit2gtk-4.1-dev`, `libsoup-3.0-dev`); not run in this environment.\n- Frontend type/lint checks not run locally; CI will exercise them.\n\n## Notes\n- `desktop:build` produces a release binary with Tauri bundling disabled in this first PR.\n- JSON5 parsing of `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` (raised by Codex on #59075) intentionally deferred — would add a new dependency; happy to do it as a follow-up.\n\nRefs #38283\nRefs #75",
